  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Federal money laundering charges\n- Potential felony conviction\n- Significant fines\n- Possible prison time (often several years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Seizure of illegally obtained assets\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Potential civil asset forfeiture\n\n3. Additional legal consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Potential immigration consequences\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Frequency of the activity\n- Individual's criminal history\n- Jurisdiction and specific circumstances\n\nProsecution can occur at both state and federal levels, with federal charges typically being more severe.",
